Data were analyzed using IBM SPSS Statistics for Macintosh, Version 28.0. Armonk, NY: IBM Corp. Intention to treat analysis was used. Data were assessed for normality using the Kolmogorov–Smirnov test. Age, dmf, and the number of treated teeth were presented using mean and standard deviation. The study outcomes were the counts of S. mutans and lactobacilli after one month and the number of active caries lesions (dependent variables). Bacterial counts and percent reduction in bacteria were presented as median and interquartile range (IQR). Categorical variables were presented using frequency and percentage. The percent change in the bacterial count was calculated using the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
